## Plans Repository

Design docs and implementation plans are stored centrally in `~/workspace/git/Implementations/`, **not** inside individual repos.

- **Location**: `Implementations/<repo-name>/plans/<date>-<topic>.md`
- **Structure**: One subfolder per repo (e.g. `NerpyBot/plans/`), files named by date and topic
- **Why**: Keeps repos clean; plans are gitignored per-repo anyway — centralizing them makes them findable and versioned

When creating a new plan, always write it to the Implementations repo, not to `docs/plans/` or any local plans folder inside the project repo.

Note: `~/.claude/plans/` is Claude Code's **internal plan mode storage** - do not flag it as misplaced. This rule only applies to plans/specs created inside repos (e.g. by the superpowers skill).

